This pull request introduces automated CSS linting to the project and improves the code quality workflow. The main changes include adding Stylelint configuration, updating the workflow to include CSS linting, and updating project scripts and dependencies.

**Workflow and Automation Improvements:**

* Renamed the GitHub Actions workflow from `Prettier Check` to `Code Quality Check` and updated the job name to `code-quality` for broader code quality coverage. (.github/workflows/prettier.yml)
* Added a new step to the workflow to run CSS linting using the `yarn lint` command, ensuring CSS code quality is checked on pull requests. (.github/workflows/prettier.yml)

**CSS Linting Integration:**

* Added a Stylelint configuration file (`.stylelintrc.json`) with recommended rules and customizations to enforce CSS best practices.
* Updated `package.json` to add `lint` and `lint:fix` scripts for running and auto-fixing Stylelint issues, and added Stylelint along with related configuration packages to `devDependencies`.Adds stylelint configuration and integrates it into the code quality workflow. This ensures consistent styling and helps catch potential CSS errors, improving the overall maintainability and quality of the codebase.

commits.message:
Add HashRedirect component for hash-based routing

Introduced a new HashRedirect component to handle URL hashes starting with '#/' and redirect them to the corresponding path using Next.js router. Integrated HashRedirect into the RootLayout to ensure hash-based navigation is supported across the app.

Refactor ImageView to use CSS modules and improve loading UX

Replaced the global SCSS for ImageView with a CSS module for better style encapsulation. Updated the ImageView component to show a loader while the image is loading and improved accessibility and styling. Adjusted CardRead and Header styles for responsive image sizing and z-index.

Add responsive utility and update search button rendering

Introduced a universal Responsive component and useMediaQuery hook for breakpoint-based rendering. Updated Header to render ButtonSearch only on desktop using the new Responsive component, and removed device detection logic from ButtonSearch.

Refactor NewsBlock to use CSS modules and update API usage

Renamed NewsBlock.scss to NewsBlock.module.scss and updated class names for CSS modules. Refactored NewsBlock.tsx to import the new module, improved error handling, and updated the articles API usage to use the new getArticles signature. Also updated the ArticlePage to use getArticles instead of getAllArticles.

Improve accessibility theme options and UI styles

Added light and dark theme options to the accessibility mode theme selector. Updated related SCSS for better theme distinction and button styling, including use of !important for font size. Minor code style improvements in HashRedirect and Responsive components, and fixed indentation in NewsBlock error rendering. Added margin to modal content for improved layout.

Add theme overlay variable and update modal backgrounds

Introduced the --color-overlay CSS variable to all theme files for consistent overlay backgrounds. Updated ImageViewerModal and Modal components to use this variable and enabled backdrop blur for improved visual appearance. Adjusted some color and border styles for better theme integration.

Remove ScrollToTop and improve scroll disabling

Deleted the ScrollToTop component and enhanced the useDisableScroll hook to handle scrollbar compensation by adjusting padding. Also updated DatePicker styles for better label spacing and removed unnecessary gap in the container.

Remove API_BASE usage from form submissions

Updated FeedbackForm and ReviewForm to use relative API endpoints instead of the API_BASE constant for fetch requests. This simplifies API calls and improves portability across environments.

Rename Filesbox to filesbox in search results

Standardizes the property name from 'Filesbox' to 'filesbox' in SearchResultsType and its usage in the search page for consistency and to avoid potential bugs due to case sensitivity.

Refactor article and employee card components to CSS modules

Replaced the 'card-read' article card components with new 'article-card' components using CSS modules for improved style encapsulation. Updated all references in pages and widgets to use the new components. Similarly, refactored the employee card to use CSS modules, added skeleton loaders with modular styles, and updated loader component to use CSS modules. Removed old SCSS files and legacy components.

Refactor color variables and update styles for theme consistency

Replaces deprecated color variables (e.g., --font-color-light, --font-color-gray) with new semantic variables (--font-color-primary, --font-color-secondary, etc.) across all SCSS and module files for improved theme consistency. Updates theme files to use the new variables and adds missing gray shades. Refactors related React components and skeletons to match updated class names and style conventions. Removes unused EmployeeCard.scss in favor of module SCSS. This improves maintainability and enables more flexible theming.

Add CSS tokens for color variables

Introduced a new _tokens.scss file with CSS custom properties for error, warning, success, and info colors. Updated error page styles to use the new error color variable and imported tokens into the main stylesheet for consistent usage.

Refactor notifications to use CSS modules

Migrated notification styles from SCSS to CSS modules for better encapsulation and maintainability. Updated Notification and NotificationContainer components to use CSS modules and clsx for dynamic class names. Removed NotificationButtons component and its export from the index file.

Refactor theme variables and remove ButtonTheme styles

Replaced 'background-panel' and 'background-panel-item' variables with 'background-footer' and 'background-footer-item' across all theme files for consistency. Updated Footer and Tabs components to use the new variables. Removed unused ButtonTheme.scss and its import from buttonTheme.tsx.

issue.title: 2172: Support external keyboard usage
issue.body:
### Short Description
Currently not all elements can be navigated easily with external keyboard (for ex. Bluetooth or usb), the problem still exists because of the WebView [(existing issue)](https://github.com/react-native-webview/react-native-webview/issues/2326) and cannot be fully fixed because of this, additionally TextInput from react-native has an  [issue](https://github.com/facebook/react-native/issues/31820) with focusing. Thus [react-native-external-keyboard](https://github.com/ArturKalach/react-native-external-keyboard) has been used to solve the issue with TextInput.
### Proposed Changes

<!-- Describe this PR in more detail. -->

- Use react-native-external-keyboard to solve the issue with TextInput for now untill we switch to react-native 0.80.0 version where this issue has been fixed
- DatePickerInput.tsx has been fixed
- EventsDateFilter.tsx has been adjusted to hide it from keyboard navigation when it is closed
- SearchInput has been changed to focus on the input because there is a problem with tab being stuck in Back button (solution: to autofocus on the input)
- TextButton.tsx has been adjusted to be able to focus after WebView on export calendar button with tab on event when it is scrolled to footer 

### Side Effects

- should be none

### Testing

Test all the components using external keyboard by navigating using Tab, arrow down, arrow up, arrow left and right keys

### Resolved Issues

<!-- List all issues which should be closed when this PR is merged. -->

Fixes: #2172
